{"entryType":"AA","primaryAccession":"UPI000000001C-397342","uniProtkbId":null,"annotationScore":0.0,"proteinDescription":{"recommendedName":{"fullName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"RuleBase","id":"RU365101"}],"value":"DNA topoisomerase I"},"ecNumbers":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"RuleBase","id":"RU365101"}],"value":"5.6.2.1"}]},"alternativeNames":[{"fullName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"RuleBase","id":"RU365101"}],"value":"DNA topoisomerase 1"}}]},"comments":[{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"ARBA","id":"ARBA00034656"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"RuleBase","id":"RU365101"}],"value":"Releases the supercoiling and torsional tension of DNA introduced during the DNA replication and transcription by transiently cleaving and rejoining one strand of the DNA duplex. Introduces a single-strand break via transesterification at the specific target site 5'-[CT]CCTTp site in duplex DNA. The scissile phosphodiester is attacked by the catalytic tyrosine of the enzyme, resulting in the formation of a DNA-(3'-phosphotyrosyl)-enzyme intermediate and the expulsion of a 5'-OH DNA strand. The free DNA strand then undergoes passage around the unbroken strand thus removing DNA supercoils. Finally, in the religation step, the DNA 5'-OH attacks the covalent intermediate to expel the active-site tyrosine and restore the DNA phosphodiester backbone"}],"commentType":"FUNCTION"},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"ARBA","id":"ARBA00006645"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"PROSITE-ProRule","id":"PRU01382"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"RuleBase","id":"RU365101"}],"value":"Belongs to the type IB topoisomerase family"}],"commentType":"SIMILARITY"}],"features":[{"type":"Active site","location":{"start":{"value":274,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":274,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"O-(3'-phospho-DNA)-tyrosine intermediate","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"PROSITE-ProRule","id":"PRU01382"}]}],"keywords":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"ARBA","id":"ARBA00023125"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"PROSITE-ProRule","id":"PRU01382"}],"id":"KW-0238","category":"Molecular function","name":"DNA-binding"},{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"ARBA","id":"ARBA00023235"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"PROSITE-ProRule","id":"PRU01382"}],"id":"KW-0413","category":"Molecular function","name":"Isomerase"},{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"ARBA","id":"ARBA00022921"}],"id":"KW-0426","category":"Developmental stage","name":"Late protein"},{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"ARBA","id":"ARBA00023029"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"PROSITE-ProRule","id":"PRU01382"}],"id":"KW-0799","category":"Molecular function","name":"Topoisomerase"}],"extraAttributes":{"countByCommentType":{"FUNCTION":1,"SIMILARITY":1},"countByFeatureType":{"Active site":1}}}